ing if that excludes module opening options.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed: conscrypt-openjdk-uber is self-contained and embeds its OpenJDK native libraries. Meaningful socket/platform coverage does need Java module opens because Conscrypt 1.4.1 reflectively accesses JDK socket internals.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For tests that exercise Conscrypt socket/file-descriptor paths, configure both JVM test execution and native-image build args with: --add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED, --add-opens=java.base/java.net=ALL-UNNAMED, and --add-opens=java.base/sun.nio.ch=ALL-UNNAMED. Prefer local loopback sockets or in-memory SSLEngine handshakes; no external TLS service is required. Use Conscrypt.checkAvailability() and Conscrypt.newProvider() in tests so native library loading is exercised.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The 1.4.1 artifact is old and its bundled native library may expose JDK 25/native-image compatibility issues that setup cannot fix.\",\n    \"Conscrypt extracts its bundled JNI library to a temporary/work directory at runtime; only set org.conscrypt.native.workdir if local verification shows the default temp directory is unavailable or mounted noexec.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_039aab2e02b04d5f016a42f427fa488190aa2d67d6d29353e0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2834, "output": 1165, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40863, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782772754979, "responseId": "resp_039aab2e02b04d5f016a42f4142450819080df8e864811ff80"}, "toolResults": []}
